EXPLAIN select p.c1,e.c1 from t3 e inner join t4 p on e.c0 = p.c0 and e.c1 = p.c1 and hex(e.c0) = hex(p.c0);
Query Plan
===================================================
|ID|OPERATOR           |NAME|EST.ROWS|EST.TIME(us)|
---------------------------------------------------
|0 |MERGE JOIN         |    |2       |6           |
|1 |├─TABLE FULL SCAN  |p   |1       |3           |
|2 |└─SORT             |    |2       |3           |
|3 |  └─TABLE FULL SCAN|e   |2       |3           |
===================================================
Outputs & filters:
-------------------------------------
  0 - output([p.c1], [e.c1]), filter(nil), rowset=16
      equal_conds([e.c0 = p.c0], [e.c1 = p.c1], [hex(e.c0) = hex(p.c0)]), other_conds(nil)
      merge_directions([ASC], [ASC], [ASC])
  1 - output([p.c0], [p.c1]), filter(nil), rowset=16
      access([p.c0], [p.c1]), partitions(p0)
      is_index_back=false, is_global_index=false, 
      range_key([p.c0], [p.c1]), range(MIN,MIN ; MAX,MAX)always true
  2 - output([e.c0], [e.c1], [hex(e.c0)]), filter(nil), rowset=16
      sort_keys([e.c0, ASC], [e.c1, ASC], [hex(e.c0), ASC])
  3 - output([e.c0], [e.c1], [hex(e.c0)]), filter(nil), rowset=16
      access([e.c0], [e.c1]), partitions(p0)
      is_index_back=false, is_global_index=false, 
      range_key([e.__pk_increment]), range(MIN ; MAX)always true
